introducing trimpin arts at stanford university presented by sica home search this site arts enews subscribe featured archive gallery introducing trimpin trimpin sound sculptor engineer inventor musician and macarthur genius award winner spoke about his forthcoming work which will be developed during his 2010 2011 residency at stanford the centerpiece of stanford lively arts 2010 11 season memory forward will be the world premiere of the lively arts commissioned gurs zyklus the gurs cycle on may 14 2011 created by the seattle based inventor sculptor musician trimpin in collaboration with director and vocalist rinde eckert the multimedia installation and performance will conclude a yearlong engagement by trimpin with stanford faculty and students notably at the center for computer research in music and acoustics ccrma in this installation and performance different mediums will be explored by synchronizing speech voice sound video projection sculpture and historical elements the project will draw audiences through the history and landscape of gurs an internment camp near the french spanish border where trimpin's mentor the composer conlon nancarrow had been interned and to where many of the jews in trimpin's hometown had been deported during wwii throughout the months leading up to the premiere trimpin will work with and teach at stanford's center for research in music and acoustics ccrma which will be integral to the project lively arts website home calendar gallery news visiting artists grants organizations facilities plan a visit about sica students faculty staff make a gift volunteer login press sitemap contact connect twitter facebook vimeo flickr 2011 stanford university all rights reserved local user login
